[[Translation:en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Train is lost warning]]

A train will be reported lost if it cannot find a route to the station it is currently heading to. See also [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Advanced Settings/Vehicles#warn-if-train-is-lost]].

== Description ==

You can click on the message to center the main screen over the train in order to fix the problem.
<center>[[File:en/Losttrain.png|center|frame|Train 1 is lost.]]</center>

Trains usually get lost because:
* A [[en/Manual/Signals]] is placed on the wrong side.
* A piece of track has been destroyed due to a mistake or a [[en/Manual/Disasters]].
* The train's destination is not connected to the railway track that the train is on.

